(15537, 'nitroglycerin transdermal system', 'N/A', 'contraindicated', 'Drug Interactions The vasodilating effects of nitroglycerin may be additive with those of other vasodilators. Concomitant use of Nitroglycerin Transdermal Systems with phosphodiesterase inhibitors in any form is contraindicated (see CONTRAINDICATIONS). Concomitant use of Nitroglycerin Transdermal Systems with riociguat, a soluble guanylate cyclase stimulator, is contraindicated (see CONTRAINDICATIONS).', 'DailyMed'),
