(6420, 'labetalol hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'minor', 'The anesthesiologist should be informed when a patient is receiving labetalol.Labetalol blunts the reflex tachycardia produced by nitroglycerin without preventing its hypotensive effect. If labetalol is used with nitroglycerin in patients with angina pectoris, additional antihypertensive effects may occur.Care should be taken if labetalol is used concomitantly with calcium channel antagonists of the verapamil type.', 'DailyMed'),
(6420, 'nitroglycerin', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Nitroglycerin acts directly on vascular muscle. Marked symptomatic orthostatic hypotension has been reported when calcium channel blockers and oral controlled-release nitroglycerin were used in combination.', 'DailyMed');
